This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the use of Markov Random Fields (MRFs) in computer vision and proposes a technique to improve MRF inference. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a discriminative rule to find optimal solutions for a subset of variables. The paper also mentions the use of pre-processing techniques in MRF inference, which could place it in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the guarantees of the proposed technique, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
